Again it is a certain truth that the sun is really about the same size as it appears to us to be : see Epic. 1. l. 91, Lucr. v 564—591 : because from the experiments you can make with fire here on earth and the fact that so long as it is visible it does not diminish in size, but sooner indeed loses its brightness, you can by reason and induction apply these facts to the sun and the stars.
